Robert Bates is charged with second-degree manslaughter for accidentally shooting Eric Harris on April 2 . 
  He is accused of firing his gun instead of his Taser in a botched undercover operation . 
  Sources in the Tulsa County Sheriff's Office claim that Bates was not properly trained to be a reserve deputy . 
  They say three of his supervisors were removed from their jobs after they refused to sign off on his training hours . 
  Bates has been charged with manslaughter for the death of Harris . 
  The 73-year-old has been classified as an 'advanced reserve deputy' and is free on $25,000 bail . 
  Sheriff Stanley Glanz has said Bates was 'paid to play cop'